: Slips with notes and exercises inserted (paginated pp.91-92 and pp.199-200).</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Former shelfmark: British Museum, London "No. 70. Grammatical works by Abu Suud, al-Zanjani, &amp; Ibn Jinni." ; "٦٣٣" on tail of textblock.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Binding: Pasteboards faced in marbled paper (blue and salmon) with spine, fore-edge flap and edges/turn-ins in dark red leather (marbled paper faced, leather edged, framed binding) ; Type II binding (with flap) ; board linings in laid paper ; sewn in pink thread, two stations ; in poor condition with much abrasion, lifting and losses of paper and leather, delamination of boards, pest damage, etc.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Support: European laid paper with 9 laid lines per cm. (horizontal) and chain lines spaced 28 mm. apart ; watermarks include triple mount with bird in profile in circle (compare Piccard no.153741 and 153742) ; well-sized and burnished ; much staining.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Decoration: Keywords, some titles, section headings, and some glosses rubricated ; textual dividers in the form of red discs ; written area of incipit page surrounded by gold frame, written area elsewhere surrounded by red rule-border.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Script: Large, bold naskh-nastaʻlīq (talik) ; sans serif ; characteristic descent of words to baseline ; sweeping descenders and elongated horizontal strokes.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Layout: Written in 13 and roughly 7 lines per page ; written area of third work divided to three columns with verbs appearing in the two outer columns and elucidation on the diagonal in the center column ; frame-ruled.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Collation: i, 10 V(100), IV+3 (111), i ; chiefly quinions ; catchwords present ; pagination in pencil, Western numerals, supplied during digitization.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Incipit: "قال المفتقر الى الله الودود احمد بن علي ابن مسعود غفر الله له ولوالديه واحسن اليهما واليه اعلم ان الصرف ام العلوم والنحو ابوها ..."</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Title supplied by cataloguer.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Ms. codex.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">8. p.226-p.228 : [originally left blank, now carries excerpts, exercises, owners' marks, etc.].</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">7. p.194-p.225 : Mithāl al-amthilah al-mukhtalifah.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">6. p.192-p.193 : [originally left blank, now carries excerpts, exercises, etc.].</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">6. p.172-p.191 : [Bināʼ al-afʻāl].</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">5. p.170-p.171 : [originally left blank].</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">4. p.132-p.169 : [Kitāb al-Maqṣūd fī al-taṣrīf].</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">3. p.130-p.131 : [originally left blank, now carries excerpts, etc.].</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">2. p.93-p.129 : Kitāb al-ʻIzzī / ʻAbd al-Wahhāb ibn Ibrāhīm al-Zanjānī.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">1. p.4-p.90 : [Marāḥ al-arwāḥ] / Aḥmad ibn ʻAlī Ibn Masʻūd.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="510" ind1="4" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Brockelmann, C. GAL,</subfield><subfield code="c">I 131 ; SI 191</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="510" ind1="4" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Brockelmann, C. GAL,</subfield><subfield code="c">I 283</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="510" ind1="4" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Brockelmann, C. GAL,</subfield><subfield code="c">II 21</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="520" ind1="8" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Short collection (majmūʻah / mecmua) of grammatical works on Arabic morphology including Ibn Masʻūd's Marāḥ al-arwāḥ and Taṣrīf al-Zanjānī, along with the anonymous Kitāb al-Maqṣūd, Kitāb al-Bināʼ, and Mithāl al-amthilah al-mukhtalifah.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="538" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Mode of access: Internet.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="541" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="c">Purchase ;</subfield><subfield code="a">Acquired by purchase (funds donated by Horace Rackham).</subfield><subfield code="d">1924.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="546" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Arabic.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="561" ind1=" " ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Bookplate of British Museum, London on interior of upper cover, "British Museum, London. No. 70. Grammatical works by Abu Suud, al-Zanjani, &amp; Ibn Jinni." ; circular waqf-seal impression in black ink appears on ’title page’ (p.3) and several places throughout, reads: "هذا وقف الراجي فيض الصمدي الشيخ احمد ضيا الدين ابن مصطفى الخالدي فمن بدله بعد ما سمعه فانما اثمه على الذين يبدلونه" in name of Aḥmad Ḍiyāʼ al-Dīn ibn Muṣṭafá al-Khālidī (i.e. Ahmed Ziyâüddîn Gümüşhanevî, d. 1893 or 4) ; numerous ownership statements and seal impressions on p.3, p.93, p.171 and pp.225-228, particularly in the name of one Mustafa Efendi ; dated statements appear on p.225 "ما شاء الله سلطان سليم كتابت [كتاب؟] مصطفى افندى اوستاذ احمد افندى بدروس ... جا سنه ۱۱٩١" (dated Jumādá I 1191 [June-July 1777]) and on p.227 "... في ۱۰ م سنه ۱۱۹۲" (dated 10 Muḥarram 1192 [ca. 8 February 1778]) ; numerous glosses and marginal corrections.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="650" ind1=" " ind2="0"><subfield code="a">Manuscripts, Arabic</subfield><subfield code="z">Michigan</subfield><subfield code="z">Ann Arbor.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="650" ind1=" " ind2="0"><subfield code="a">Arabic language</subfield><subfield code="x">Verb</subfield><subfield code="v">Early works to 1800.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="650" ind1=" " ind2="0"><subfield code="a">Arabic language</subfield><subfield code="x">Morphology</subfield><subfield code="v">Early works to 1800.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="650" ind1=" " ind2="0"><subfield code="a">Arabic language</subfield><subfield code="x">Grammar</subfield><subfield code="v">Early works to 1800.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="700" ind1="1" ind2=" "><subfield code="6">880-04</subfield><subfield code="a">Zanjānī, ʻAbd al-Wahhāb ibn Ibrāhīm,</subfield><subfield code="d">active 1257.</subfield><subfield code="t">Mabādiʼ fī al-taṣrīf.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="740" ind1="0" ind2="2"><subfield code="6">880-08</subfield><subfield code="a">Bināʼ al-afʻāl.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="740" ind1="0" ind2="2"><subfield code="6">880-07</subfield><subfield code="a">مقصود في التصريف</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="740" ind1="0" ind2="2"><subfield code="6">880-06</subfield><subfield code="a">مثال الامثلة المختلفة</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="740" ind1="0" ind2="2"><subfield code="6">880-05</subfield><subfield code="a">عزي</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="773" ind1="0" ind2=" "><subfield code="a">Tiflis Collection.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="880" ind1="0" ind2="2"><subfield code="6">740-08/</subfield><subfield code="a">بناء الافعال.</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="880" ind1="0" ind2="2"><subfield code="6">740-07/</subfield><subfield code="a">Maqṣūd fī al-taṣrīf</subfield></datafield><datafield tag="880" ind1="0" ind2="2"><subfield code="6">740-06/</subfield><sub